Scientists from the University of California at Berkeley prove that if Walmart raises the average salary to $ 12 per hour, it will cost the corporation $ 3.2 billion.
That's about 1.1% more than she spends on a paycheck now.
If Walmart completely shifts the growth of wages on the shoulders of customers, then each visit to the store will cost them only 46 cents more.
For a year, they will spend some 12.39 dollars more than now.
Walmart supporters note that the protests occurred in just nine states and did not cause any minor damage to the corporation.
