The government is making efforts not to build so many small housing.
For example, it has begun to affect the real estate sector.
The Urban Development Guide has moved to controlling the number of small apartments, known as "shoeboxes," that can be built in certain areas of the city.
This apartment of 46 square meters sells very well.
